	<a name="startcontent"></a>
	<h1>Checklist for carers</h1>
	
<ul class="anchorlinks"></ul>
<div>

<div class="topic">
<p>The lists and links below are to help you to check out all the main services
and entitlements for carers.</p>

<div>
<p><script type="text/javascript">
document.write("If you would like these links to remain available while you browse this website, you can <a href='#' class='secNavLink' data='carers'>'pin' the checklist to the right-hand side of the website</a>. It will remain in place until you click the 'X' in the top right-hand corner.");</script></p>
</div>

<p>The headings in the left hand column of each section link to general
documents on the subject, and those in the right hand column link to details of
specific payments or services.</p>

<p></p>

<p><strong>Payments to carers</strong></p>

<table border="1" cellpadding="5"><col width="200"><col width="400"><tbody><tr><td><p><a href="../../social_welfare/social_welfare_payments/carers/payments_to_carers.html">Overview
        of payments to carers</a> </p>

        <p>There is a 50% extra payment if caring for 2 or more people.</p>
      </td>
      <td><p><a href="../../social_welfare/social_welfare_payments/carers/carers_benefit.html">Carer's
        Benefit</a> (may be paid consecutively for 2 different people)</p>

        <p><a href="../../social_welfare/social_welfare_payments/carers/carers_allowance.html">Carer's
        Allowance</a></p>

        <p><a href="../../social_welfare/social_welfare_payments/carers/half_rate_carers_allowance.html">Half-rate
        Carer's Allowance</a></p>

        <p><a href="../../social_welfare/social_welfare_payments/disability_and_illness/domiciliary_care_allowance.html">Domiciliary
        Care Allowance</a></p>
      </td>
    </tr></tbody></table><p></p>

<p><strong>Extra payments</strong></p>

<table border="1" cellpadding="5"><col width="200"><col width="400"><tbody><tr><td><p><a href="../../social_welfare/social_welfare_payments/extra_social_welfare_benefits/additional_social_welfare_benefits.html">Additional
        social welfare benefits</a> </p>

        <p></p>

        <p></p>
      </td>
      <td><p><a href="../../social_welfare/social_welfare_payments/extra_social_welfare_benefits/free_travel.html">Free
        travel</a> </p>

        <p><a href="../../social_welfare/social_welfare_payments/extra_social_welfare_benefits/household_benefits_package.html">Household
        Benefits Package</a></p>

        <p><a href="../../social_welfare/social_welfare_payments/extra_social_welfare_benefits/fuel_allowance.html">Fuel
        Allowance</a></p>

        <p><a href="../../social_welfare/social_welfare_payments/carers/respite_care_grant.html">Carer's Support Grant (formerly called Respite Care Grant)</a></p>
      </td>
    </tr><tr><td><p></p>

        <p><a href="../../social_welfare/social_welfare_payments/supplementary_welfare_schemes/supplementary_welfare_allow.html">Supplementary
        Welfare Allowance Scheme</a></p>

        <p></p>
      </td>
      <td><p><a href="../../social_welfare/social_welfare_payments/supplementary_welfare_schemes/rent_supplement.html">Rent
        Supplement</a></p>

        <p><a href="../../social_welfare/social_welfare_payments/supplementary_welfare_schemes/diet_and_heating_supplements.html">Heating
        Supplement</a></p>

        <p><a href="../../social_welfare/social_welfare_payments/supplementary_welfare_schemes/exceptional_needs_payments.html">Exceptional
        and Urgent Needs Payment</a></p>

        <p><a href="../../social_welfare/social_welfare_payments/social_welfare_payments_to_families_and_children/back_to_school_clothing_and_footwear_allowance.html">Back
        to School Clothing and Footwear Allowance</a></p>
      </td>
    </tr></tbody></table><p></p>

<p><strong>Other</strong></p>

<table border="1" cellpadding="5"><col width="200"><col width="400"><tbody><tr><td><p>Employment law for carers </p>
      </td>
      <td><p><a href="../../employment/employment_rights_and_conditions/leave_and_holidays/carers_leave_from_employment.html">Carer's
        leave</a> </p>
      </td>
    </tr><tr><td><p>Keeping your social insurance record up to date</p>
      </td>
      <td><p><a href="../../social_welfare/irish_social_welfare_system/social_insurance_prsi/homemakers_scheme.html">Homemaker's
        Scheme</a> (PRSI record)</p>

        <p><a href="../../social_welfare/irish_social_welfare_system/social_insurance_prsi/credited_social_insurance_contributions.html">Credited
        social insurance contributions</a> (PRSI record)</p>
      </td>
    </tr><tr><td></td>
      <td><p><a href="../../health/care_in_your_community/community_care_services.html">Access
        to HSE supports</a></p>

        <p></p>

        <p><strong>Working/studying while caring</strong></p>

        <p>You can work or study for up to 15 hours a week and keep your
        carer's payment. Income earned may be taken into account for Carer's
        Allowance.</p>

        <p><strong>When caring finishes</strong></p>

        <p>You may qualify for an <a href="../../employment/unemployment_and_redundancy/employment_support_schemes/schemes_to_support_employment.html">employment
        scheme</a> or an <a href="../../education/returning_to_education/sources_of_information_on_returning_to_education.html">education
        scheme</a>.</p>
      </td>
    </tr></tbody></table><p></p>

<p><strong>Tax credits</strong></p>

<table border="1" cellpadding="5"><col width="200"><col width="400"><tbody><tr><td>Specific tax credits and allowances</td>
      <td><p><a href="../../money_and_tax/tax/income_tax_credits_and_reliefs/home_carers_tax_credit.html">Home
        carer's tax credit</a> </p>

        <p><a href="../../money_and_tax/tax/tax_credits_and_reliefs_for_people_with_disabilities/tax_relief_for_employing_a_home_carer.html">Tax
        allowance to employ a carer</a></p>

        <p><a href="../../money_and_tax/tax/tax_credits_and_reliefs_for_people_with_disabilities/incapacitated_child_tax_credit.html">Incapacitated
        Child Credit</a></p>
      </td>
    </tr></tbody></table></div>
<div id="lastupdated" class="extra"><em><strong>Page edited:</strong> 13 January 2015</em></div></div>
